---
const title = "Eqho | Free Offline Voice-to-Text Dictation";
const description = "Free, offline voice-to-text dictation. Powered by OpenAI's Whisper, running 100% locally and GPU-accelerated on NVIDIA, AMD, or Intel. Press a hotkey and dictate into any app.";
const author = "Daniel Mevit";
const year = 2026; 
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{title}</title>
    
    <!-- Tab Icons for Light Mode Tabs -->
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="32x32" href="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/DanielMevit/eqho/main/assets/logo_32_dark.png" media="(prefers-color-scheme: light)" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="64x64" href="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/DanielMevit/eqho/main/assets/logo_64_dark.png" media="(prefers-color-scheme: light)" />

    <!-- Tab Icons for Dark Mode Tabs -->
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="32x32" href="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/DanielMevit/eqho/main/assets/logo_32_white.png" media="(prefers-color-scheme: dark)" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="64x64" href="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/DanielMevit/eqho/main/assets/logo_64_white.png" media="(prefers-color-scheme: dark)" />

    <meta name="description" content={description} />
    <meta name="keywords" content="speech to text, voice to text, dictation software, offline speech recognition, free dictation app, voice typing for Windows, OpenAI Whisper app, whisper.cpp GUI, faster-whisper GUI, Vulkan speech to text, AMD GPU dictation, AMD Radeon voice to text, Intel Arc dictation, cross-vendor GPU transcription, runs on any GPU, private speech to text, local voice recognition, no-cloud transcription" />
    <meta name="author" content={author} />

    <!-- Inter Font -->
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

    <!-- Open Graph for Link Sharing -->
    <meta property="og:title" content={title} />
    <meta property="og:description" content={description} />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://danielmevit.github.io/eqho/" />
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/DanielMevit/eqho/main/logo/logo_horizontal_dark.png" />
    <meta property="og:site_name" content="Eqho" />

    <!-- Structured data for search engines + AI scrapers (SoftwareApplication) -->
    <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
      {
        "@context": "https://schema.org",
        "@type": "SoftwareApplication",
        "name": "Eqho",
        "applicationCategory": "UtilitiesApplication",
        "operatingSystem": "Windows 10 (64-bit), Windows 11 (64-bit), macOS, Linux",
        "description": "Free, offline voice-to-text dictation powered by OpenAI's Whisper. Press a hotkey, speak, and your words appear in any app — 100% local, GPU-accelerated on NVIDIA, AMD, and Intel.",
        "url": "https://danielmevit.github.io/eqho/",
        "downloadUrl": "https://github.com/DanielMevit/eqho/releases",
        "softwareVersion": "0.8.2",
        "author": { "@type": "Person", "name": "Daniel Mevit" },
        "license": "https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html",
        "isAccessibleForFree": true,
        "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "price": "0", "priceCurrency": "USD" },
        "keywords": "speech to text, voice typing, offline dictation, OpenAI Whisper, whisper.cpp, faster-whisper, Vulkan speech to text, AMD GPU dictation, AMD Radeon voice to text, Intel Arc dictation, cross-vendor GPU transcription, runs on any GPU, private speech to text, local voice recognition, no-cloud transcription"
      }
    </script>

    <style>
      :root {
        /* GitHub Dark Theme Palette */
        --color-bg: #0d1117;
        --color-card-bg: #161b22;
        --color-text: #c9d1d9;
        --color-heading: #ffffff;
        --color-blue: #58a6ff;
        --color-muted: #8b949e;
        --color-border: #30363d;
        --color-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
        --color-hover: #1f242c;
      }

      body {
        font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
        background-color: var(--color-bg);
        color: var(--color-text);
        line-height: 1.6;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
      }

      main {
        max-width: 960px;
        margin: 8rem auto;
        padding: 0 2rem;
      }

      h1, h2, h3 {
        color: var(--color-heading);
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 3.5rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
        margin: 0;
      }

      h2 {
        font-size: 2rem;
        font-weight: 500;
        margin-top: 5rem;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
      }

      h3 {
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        font-weight: 500;
        margin-top: 3rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        color: var(--color-blue);
      }

      p { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }

      ul { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; }
      li { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }

      a {
        color: var(--color-blue);
        text-decoration: none;
      }

      a:hover {
        text-decoration: underline;
      }

      /* Logo and Header Styling */
      header {
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 6rem;
      }

      .header-title-container {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        gap: 1.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      }

      .logo-link {
        display: flex;
      }

      .logo-img {
        width: 160px; 
        height: auto;
      }

      .header-desc {
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        color: var(--color-muted);
        max-width: 680px;
        margin: 0 auto 1.5rem auto;
      }

      /* Platform Icons Row */
      .platform-icons {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 2rem;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
      }

      .platform-icons svg {
        width: 28px;
        height: 28px;
        fill: var(--color-muted);
        transition: fill 0.2s ease;
      }

      .platform-icons svg:hover {
        fill: var(--color-text);
      }

      section { margin-bottom: 6rem; }

      /* Visual Showcase */
      .visual-comparison {
        margin: 4rem 0;
        text-align: center;
      }

      .visual-comparison img {
        max-width: 100%;
        border-radius: 8px;
        border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        box-shadow: 0 12px 24px var(--color-shadow);
      }

      .visual-caption {
        margin-top: 1.5rem;
        font-style: italic;
        color: var(--color-muted);
      }

      /* Grid for Features */
      .grid-3 {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
        gap: 2rem;
        margin-top: 3rem;
      }

      .grid-card {
        background-color: var(--color-card-bg);
        border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 2rem;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 12px var(--color-shadow);
      }

      .grid-card h3 { 
        margin-top: 0; 
        color: var(--color-heading); 
        font-weight: 600;
      }

      /* Accordion / Dropdown Styling for FAQ & Install */
      .accordion-container {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 1rem;
        margin-top: 2rem;
      }

      .accordion-item {
        background-color: var(--color-card-bg);
        border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        border-radius: 8px;
        overflow: hidden;
        transition: background-color 0.2s ease;
      }
      
      .accordion-item:hover {
        background-color: var(--color-hover);
      }

      .accordion-item summary {
        padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        font-weight: 500;
        color: var(--color-heading);
        cursor: pointer;
        list-style: none;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        align-items: center;
        user-select: none;
      }

      .accordion-item summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }

      .accordion-item summary::after {
        content: '+';
        color: var(--color-blue);
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        line-height: 1;
        font-weight: 400;
      }

      .accordion-item[open] summary {
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        background-color: var(--color-card-bg);
      }

      .accordion-item[open] summary::after { content: '−'; }

      .accordion-content {
        padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
        color: var(--color-text);
        background-color: var(--color-bg);
        border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      }

      .accordion-content p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

      /* Code Block & Copy Button Styling */
      .code-wrapper {
        position: relative;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
      }

      pre {
        background-color: var(--color-card-bg);
        border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        color: var(--color-text);
        padding: 1.5rem;
        padding-top: 2.5rem;
        border-radius: 8px;
        overflow-x: auto;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        margin: 0;
      }

      .copy-button {
        position: absolute;
        top: 0.5rem;
        right: 0.5rem;
        background-color: transparent;
        border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        color: var(--color-muted);
        border-radius: 6px;
        padding: 0.4rem;
        cursor: pointer;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        transition: all 0.2s ease;
      }

      .copy-button:hover {
        background-color: var(--color-hover);
        color: var(--color-text);
        border-color: var(--color-muted);
      }

      .copy-button svg {
        width: 16px;
        height: 16px;
        fill: currentColor;
      }

      code { 
        font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, SF Mono, Menlo, Consolas, Liberation Mono, monospace; 
      }
      
      p code, li code {
        background-color: rgba(110, 118, 129, 0.4);
        padding: 0.2em 0.4em;
        border-radius: 6px;
        font-size: 0.85em;
      }

      footer {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 8rem;
        padding: 4rem 0;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        color: var(--color-muted);
        font-size: 0.9rem;
      }

    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <header>
        <div class="header-title-container">
          <a href="https://github.com/DanielMevit/eqho" class="logo-link">
            <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/DanielMevit/eqho/main/logo/logo_horizontal_dark.png" alt="Eqho logo" class="logo-img" />
          </a>
        </div>
        
        <p class="header-desc">
          Speak anywhere your computer lets you type. Powered by OpenAI's Whisper, running 100% locally — GPU-accelerated on NVIDIA, AMD, and Intel — with zero cloud dependency.
        </p>

        <!-- Platform Icons -->
        <div class="platform-icons" aria-label="Available for Windows, macOS, and Linux">
          <!-- Windows Icon -->
          <svg viewBox="0 0 448 512" title="Windows"><path d="M0 93.7l183.6-25.3v177.4H0V93.7zm0 324.6l183.6 25.3V268.4H0v149.9zm203.8 28L448 480V268.4H203.8v177.9zm0-380.6v180.1H448V32L203.8 65.7z"/></svg>
          
          <!-- Apple/macOS Icon -->
          <svg viewBox="0 0 384 512" title="macOS"><path d="M318.7 268.7c-.2-36.7 16.4-64.4 50-84.8-18.8-26.9-47.2-41.7-84.7-44.6-35.5-2.8-74.3 20.7-88.5 20.7-15 0-49.4-19.7-76.4-19.7C63.3 141.2 4 184.8 4 273.5q0 39.3 14.4 81.2c12.8 36.7 59 126.7 107.2 125.2 25.2-.6 43-17.9 75.8-17.9 31.8 0 48.3 17.9 76.4 17.3 48.6-.7 90.4-82.5 102.7-119.3-65.2-30.7-61.7-90-62-91.3zM85.3 7.1c26.5 0 41.6 15 52.8 29.8 11.2 14.7 22.4 39.2 18.2 64.6-26.2-1.9-51.4-15.6-67.6-33.8-16.1-18.2-28.7-45.7-22.1-60.6z"/></svg>
          
          <!-- Linux (Tux) Icon -->
          <svg viewBox="0 0 448 512" title="Linux"><path d="M220.8 123.3c1 .5 1.8 1.7 3 1.7 1.1 0 2.8-.4 2.9-1.5.2-1.4-1.9-2.3-3.2-2.9-1.7-.7-3.9-1-5.5-.1-.4.2-.8.7-.6 1.1.3 1.3 2.3 1.1 3.4 1.7zm-21.9 1.7c1.2 0 2-1.2 3-1.7 1.1-.6 3.1-.4 3.5-1.7.2-.4-.2-.9-.6-1.1-1.6-.9-3.8-.6-5.5.1-1.3.6-3.4 1.5-3.2 2.9.1 1 1.8 1.5 2.8 1.5zM420 432c-1.5-94-68-158.4-98.8-193.3-7.8-8.8-14-16.3-18.7-23.7-2.6-4.1-4.7-7.9-6.3-11.5-1.2-2.6-2-5-2.7-7.2-2.3-7.2-2.9-11.8-3.3-15-5.7-44.5 13.9-88.7 17.7-97 10.9-23.4 17.9-55.9 16.5-84.5-1.3-26.6-13.8-51.9-38.3-62.5C266.3 28.5 251.4 32 237.9 32c-9.1 0-18.1-.6-27-2.1-5.1-.9-21.1-4.1-39.7-4.1-26.4 0-45.6 14.8-53.9 41.5-7.3 23.3-5 52.4 6 78 4.2 9.7 25 56 18.2 103-1.3 9.4-4.2 16.3-6.6 21-1.3 2.6-2.6 5.1-4 7.6-1.5 2.7-3 5.3-4.7 8.1-4.8 7.6-11 15.3-18.9 24.3-30.8 35-97.3 99.3-98.8 193.3-1.1 69 42.1 79.5 87 79.9l13.1.1h1.1c29 0 55.4-8.7 75.9-21.5 17.1-10.7 34.5-10.6 52.4 0 20.6 12.8 47.1 21.5 76 21.5h1.1l13.1-.1c44.8-.4 88.1-10.9 87-79.9zm-297-74.8c11.7-20 28.6-40.4 46.2-56 31-27.2 60.1-39.3 84.7-39.3 17.1 0 32.3 6.6 44 19 12 12.6 18.3 29.5 18.2 48.7-.1 18.9-8.4 34.4-18.7 44.5-10 9.8-21.5 16-33.1 21.4-16.7 7.7-33 13.9-35 25.1-3.6 20.1 20 29.2 46.3 43.1 16 8.5 33 17.4 45.4 29.4 13.9 13.5 16.6 27.2 16.7 27.9-.9 8.2-12 14.8-22.1 16-16.9 2-33.3-3-46.7-11-20.9-12.4-42.6-16.8-62.5-16.8-20.7 0-43.1 4.7-65.1 17.4-15.5 8.9-33.4 14.6-51.6 13.2-11.2-1-23.7-8-24.8-16.2.2-.6 4-15 20.3-30 14.5-13.4 33.7-23 51-32.2 24.3-12.8 46-24.3 43-41.9-2-11.8-19.1-18.3-36.6-26.4-11.9-5.5-24-11.1-34.6-18.5-12.5-8.7-25-21-25.2-46-.1-17.5 5.8-31 16-41.7l1.3-1.3zM250.7 151c-6.1-3.3-15-2.2-22.6-2.2-5 0-9.6.7-12.2 1.9-3 1.4-4.8 3.5-5.3 6-.4 2 .4 4.3 2 6.5 1.7 2.3 4.2 3.8 6.5 4.6 2.4.7 4.9 1 6.9 1.1 5.4.3 11.2-.5 16.6-2 3.8-1 7.1-2.6 9-4.8 2.2-2.5 2.7-5.4 1.7-7.9-1.1-1.9-2.2-2.9-2.6-3.2z"/></svg>
        </div>

        <div class="visual-comparison">
          <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/DanielMevit/eqho/main/assets/eqho_app_screenshot.webp" alt="Eqho dashboard dark theme screenshot, showing the live transcription overlay and local settings dashboard" />
          <p class="visual-caption">Eqho features a clean dark theme, adjustable live transcription overlay, and completely local settings dashboard.</p>
        </div>

        <p>
          <a href="https://github.com/DanielMevit/eqho">View Repository on GitHub</a>
        </p>
      </header>

      <section aria-labelledby="features">
        <h2 id="features">Core Features</h2>
        
        <div class="grid-3">
          <article class="grid-card">
            <h3>Private by Design 🔒</h3>
            <p>No cloud, no accounts, no API keys required. Your voice data never leaves your computer. Settings and history remain strictly local.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="grid-card">
            <h3>Lightning Fast ⚡</h3>
            <p>A real-time transcription preview as you speak, powered by an optimized local engine. Eqho automatically uses the fastest option your hardware supports—GPU or CPU.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="grid-card">
            <h3>Runs on Any GPU 🎮</h3>
            <p>A dual-engine design accelerates dictation on <strong>NVIDIA, AMD, and Intel</strong> graphics—CUDA via faster-whisper and Vulkan via whisper.cpp—with a CPU fallback. No NVIDIA required, and nothing to configure.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="grid-card">
            <h3>Universal Support 🌍</h3>
            <p>Inject text into any focused application—Word, Slack, or IDEs. Features 13 supported languages with one-click model swapping.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="grid-card">
            <h3>Custom Vocabulary</h3>
            <p>Teach the model your specific names, industry jargon, and acronyms to ensure perfect transcription for technical work.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="grid-card">
            <h3>Smart Voice Commands</h3>
            <p>Opt-in formatting commands allow you to say things like "new line", "period", or "delete that" for completely hands-free control.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="how-it-works">
        <h2 id="how-it-works">How It Works</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Click into any application where you want to type.</li>
          <li>Press <strong>Alt+Q</strong> (or your custom hotkey). A floating bar will show "Listening…".</li>
          <li>Speak naturally and watch the live transcription preview.</li>
          <li>Press <strong>Alt+Q</strong> again—your words are instantly typed into the active app.</li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="install">
        <h2 id="install">Installation</h2>
        <p>Choose your operating system below to get started. The first run will automatically download the default speech model (distil-large-v3, ~1.5 GB).</p>

        <div class="accordion-container">
          <!-- Windows Installation -->
          <details class="accordion-item" open>
            <summary>Windows (Recommended)</summary>
            <div class="accordion-content">
              <p>Grab the <code>Eqho-Setup-&lt;version&gt;.exe</code> from the <strong><a href="https://github.com/DanielMevit/eqho/releases">Releases page</a></strong>, double-click, and you are done. Prefer no installer? Use the portable <code>.zip</code>.</p>
              <p><strong>Requirements:</strong> 64-bit Windows 10 or 11. There is no 32-bit build — the on-device AI models require a 64-bit system.</p>
              <p><em>Note: Unsigned binaries will show a SmartScreen prompt on first run — click "More info" → "Run anyway".</em></p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <!-- macOS Installation -->
          <details class="accordion-item">
            <summary>macOS</summary>
            <div class="accordion-content">
              <p>Download the <code>.dmg</code> from the <strong><a href="https://github.com/DanielMevit/eqho/releases">Releases page</a></strong>.</p>
              <p><strong>Important:</strong> You must grant Eqho <strong>Accessibility</strong> and <strong>Input Monitoring</strong> permissions in <em>System Settings → Privacy & Security</em>. On first launch, right-click the application and select "Open" to bypass the unsigned app warning.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <!-- Linux Installation -->
          <details class="accordion-item">
            <summary>Linux</summary>
            <div class="accordion-content">
              <p>Download the <code>.tar.gz</code> from the <strong><a href="https://github.com/DanielMevit/eqho/releases">Releases page</a></strong>.</p>
              <p><strong>Requirements:</strong> Eqho needs <code>libportaudio2</code>, <code>xclip</code>, and an AppIndicator library for the system tray to run properly. Please note that global hotkeys and text injection currently target X11 (Wayland support is on the roadmap).</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <!-- Build from Source -->
          <details class="accordion-item">
            <summary>Build From Source (Python)</summary>
            <div class="accordion-content">
              <p>Requires Python 3.10+.</p>
              <div class="code-wrapper" style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                <button class="copy-button" aria-label="Copy code">
                  <svg class="copy-icon" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M0 6.75C0 5.784.784 5 1.75 5h1.5a.75.75 0 010 1.5h-1.5a.25.25 0 00-.25.25v7.5c0 .138.112.25.25.25h7.5a.25.25 0 00.25-.25v-1.5a.75.75 0 011.5 0v1.5A1.75 1.75 0 019.25 16h-7.5A1.75 1.75 0 010 14.25v-7.5z"></path><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5 1.75C5 .784 5.784 0 6.75 0h7.5C15.216 0 16 .784 16 1.75v7.5A1.75 1.75 0 0114.25 11h-7.5A1.75 1.75 0 015 9.25v-7.5zm1.75-.25a.25.25 0 00-.25.25v7.5c0 .138.112.25.25.25h7.5a.25.25 0 00.25-.25v-7.5a.25.25 0 00-.25-.25h-7.5z"></path></svg>
                  <svg class="check-icon" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" aria-hidden="true" style="display: none; color: #3fb950;"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M13.78 4.22a.75.75 0 010 1.06l-7.25 7.25a.75.75 0 01-1.06 0L2.22 9.28a.75.75 0 011.06-1.06L6 10.94l6.72-6.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0z"></path></svg>
                </button>
<pre><code>git clone https://github.com/DanielMevit/eqho.git
cd eqho
python -m venv venv && venv\Scripts\activate # Windows
# Or for Linux/macOS: source venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
python run.py</code></pre>
              </div>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="faq">
        <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        
        <div class="accordion-container">
          <details class="accordion-item">
            <summary>Is my audio uploaded anywhere?</summary>
            <div class="accordion-content">
              <p>No. Transcription runs locally via CTranslate2. The only network access required is a one-time download for the AI model you choose to use.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
          
          <details class="accordion-item">
            <summary>Does it cost anything?</summary>
            <div class="accordion-content">
              <p>No. Eqho is free, open-source, and has no premium tiers, subscriptions, or word limits.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="accordion-item">
            <summary>Does it work on AMD or Intel GPUs?</summary>
            <div class="accordion-content">
              <p>Yes. Alongside the NVIDIA (CUDA) engine, Eqho includes a cross-vendor <strong>Vulkan engine (whisper.cpp)</strong> that accelerates dictation on <strong>AMD Radeon</strong> and <strong>Intel Arc / Iris</strong> graphics—and NVIDIA too. Eqho detects your hardware and selects the fastest engine automatically; you can also choose it under <em>Settings → General → Inference Engine</em>.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="accordion-item">
            <summary>What are the system requirements?</summary>
            <div class="accordion-content">
              <p><strong>Windows:</strong> 64-bit Windows 10 or 11 — there is no 32-bit build, because the local AI models require a 64-bit system. <strong>macOS</strong> and <strong>Linux</strong> (X11) are also supported. A GPU (NVIDIA, AMD, or Intel) is recommended for speed, but Eqho falls back to CPU. The first run downloads your chosen speech model (~1.5 GB for the default).</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="accordion-item">
            <summary>How accurate is the transcription?</summary>
            <div class="accordion-content">
              <p>It utilizes Whisper-class accuracy, which is the current state of the art for open speech recognition. You can easily pick a larger model from the settings for tougher audio environments.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
          
          <details class="accordion-item">
            <summary>Where are my settings and history saved?</summary>
            <div class="accordion-content">
              <p>Settings persist in your local user config folder (<code>%APPDATA%\Eqho</code> on Windows). Your data is completely under your control and never touches the cloud.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </section>
      
    </main>
    
